{% extends "layout.html.twig" %}

{% block sub_menu %}
        <div id="phpbb-sub-header">
            <div class="fixed-width">
                <h1>Home of phpBB Development</h1>
            </div>
        </div>
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
<div class="clearfix">
    <h2>Main Projects</h2>
    <p>These are the main projects that phpBB develops.</p>
    <ul class="contribution-list">
        <li>
            <b><a href="https://github.com/phpbb/phpbb" title="phpBB">phpBB</a></b><br />
            <p>phpBB is the main bulletin board/forum software by phpBB. It currently contains phpBB and an archive of phpBB2.
            <br />
            <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/phpbb">[GitHub Repository]</a>
            <a href="https://tracker.phpbb.com/browse/PHPBB">[Tracker]</a></p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <b><a href="https://github.com/phpbb/documentation" title="Documentation">Documentation</a></b><br />
            <p>The documentation project contains end user and developer documentation for stable phpBB releases.
            <br />
            <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/documentation">[GitHub Repository]</a>
            <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/documentation/issues">[Tracker]</a></p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="clearfix">
    <h2>phpBB Sub-Projects</h2>
    <ul class="contribution-list">
        <li>
            <b><a href="https://github.com/phpbb/customisation-db" title="Titania">Titania</a></b><br />
            <p>Titania is the customisation database that is used on www.phpbb.com and international support sites.
                <br />
                <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/customisation-db">[GitHub Repository]</a>
                <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/customisation-db/issues">[Tracker]</a>
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <b><a href="https://github.com/phpbb/quickinstall" title="QuickInstall">QuickInstall</a></b><br />
            <p>QuickInstall allows you to create multiple pre-populated phpBB installations for testing or development purposes.
                <br />
                <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/quickinstall">[GitHub Repository]</a>
                <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/quickinstall/issues">[Tracker]</a>
            </p>
        </li>
        <li class="line-break">
            <b><a href="https://github.com/phpbb/epv" title="EPV">EPV</a></b><br />
            <p>The Extension Pre-Validator is a validation tool used for pre validating extensions when submitting them to the database at phpBB.com.
                <br />
                <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/epv">[GitHub Repository]</a>
                <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/epv/issues">[Tracker]</a>
            </p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div>
    <h2>Archived Sub-Projects</h2>
    <ul class="contribution-list">
        <li>
            <b><a href="https://github.com/phpbb/automod" title="AutoMOD">AutoMOD</a></b><br />
            <p>AutoMOD was a tool for installing and removing phpBB MODifications on phpBB 3.0. It is no longer actively maintained.
                <br />
                <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/automod">[GitHub Repository]</a>
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <b><a href="https://github.com/phpbb/support-toolkit" title="STK">Support Toolkit</a></b><br />
            <p>The support toolkit was a tool that could be used to repair your board's database and files. It is no longer actively maintained.
                <br />
                <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/support-toolkit">[GitHub Repository]</a>
            </p>
        </li>
        <li class="line-break">
            <b><a href="https://github.com/phpbb/modx_creator_phpbb" title="phpBB MODX Creator">MODX Creator phpBB</a></b><br />
            <p>The phpBB MODX Creator adds a MODX install.xml file creation tool to your phpBB installation. It allows you to enter the information then turns it into an XML file. It is no longer actively maintained.
                <br />
                <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/modx_creator_phpbb">[GitHub Repository]</a>
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <b><a href="https://github.com/phpbb/modx_creator_offline" title="Offline MODX Creator">MODX Creator Offline</a></b><br />
            <p>The Offline MODX Creator is a standalone MODX install.xml file creation tool. It allows you to enter the information then turns it into an XML file. It is no longer actively maintained.
                <br />
                <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/modx_creator_offline">[GitHub Repository]</a>
            </p>
        </li>
        <li class="line-break">
            <b><a href="https://github.com/phpbb/umil" title="UMIL">UMIL</a></b><br />
            <p>UMIL is a project that MODs use to create install files to execute SQL queries and purge cache. It is no longer actively maintained.
                <br />
                <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/umil">[GitHub Repository]</a>
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <b><a href="https://github.com/phpbb/modx" title="MODX">MODX</a></b><br />
            <p>MODX is the standard for install instructions and meta-data file for phpBB Modifications. It is no longer actively maintained.
                <br />
                <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/modx">[GitHub Repository]</a>
            </p>
        </li>
        <li class="line-break">
            <b><a href="https://github.com/phpbb/mpv" title="MPV">MPV</a></b><br />
            <p>The Modification Pre-Validator is a validation tool that checks for common basic errors. It is no longer actively maintained.
                <br />
                <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/mpv">[GitHub Repository]</a>
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <b><a href="https://github.com/phpbb/modx_editor" title="MODX Editor">MODX Editor</a></b><br />
            <p>The MODX Editor is a desktop application that allows you to modify MODX files. It is no longer actively maintained.
                <br />
                <a href="https://github.com/phpbb/modx_editor">[GitHub Repository]</a>
            </p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
{% endblock %}
